FBIS4-42563 "drweu108_o_94010" FBIS-WEU-94-108 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 CYPRUS Sexual Contact Blamed for Increase in AIDS Cases Sexual Contact Blamed for Increase in AIDS Cases NC0206071594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 0430 GMT 2 Jun 94 NC0206071594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] The number of AIDS cases has shown a significant increase this year. The number of Cypriots who are new carriers of the AIDS virus increased to 13 during the first five months of 1994, compared to three cases during the same period last year. Four new cases of carriers of the AIDS virus were discovered last month: three men and one woman. In all cases, the infection was spread through sexual contact.
